Good vibes are simply higher states of vibration.
The terms good and positive are used interchangeably to describe
something desirable. For example, every time you label a past event as a
good or positive experience, you’re referring to it in this way because it
went as you’d hoped – or at least not as badly as it could have.
Essentially, you want the things you want because they make you feel good.
All of life’s desires are pursued to bring about a pleasurable emotional state
and to avoid displeasure. Most of us believe that attaining our desires will
lead to happiness.
Given that emotion is one of the most powerful vibrations you can control,
and, fundamentally, positive emotions are what we’re in search of, we can
infer that our quest in life is to experience good vibrations. Think about it:
when you feel good, your life also appears to be good. If you could
continuously experience good vibes, you’d always view your life in a
positive light.
